Program: A History of Ideas
Title: Giles Fraser on Wittgenstein and Blade Runner
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b04ykktv
Last Broadcast Date: Fri 1 Feb 2019
Giles Fraser thinks being human isn't a matter of biology or some unique attribute like language. It's not to do with what we are but about how we treat each other. Taking the work of the philosopher Wittgenstein he argues that to be human is to be considered worthy of certain kinds of respect and moral compassion. For Giles, human is a moral category and it is an instruction to treat each other well. Show less